@mvanbeusekom PhotoKit definitely seems promising. However, we'd still want to support `UIImagePickerController` for camera support. Being able to launch the camera from within the app is definitely a desirable workflow for a lot of apps.

Since PhotoKit also supports some basic image editing functionality, it could possibly also reduce the need for other plugins like `image_editor` (at least on iOS).

I've submitted PR https://github.com/flutter/plugins/pull/3090 to remove the permissions requirement from `image_picker` (through an iOS-specific option).

My app crash in simulator (iOS), always after second use of image_picker.
I have latest flutter and image_picker lib.

@Adrift001 Do you have some solution for this?

